OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1779329020
OL,3,CBBL practitioner admits procedures
OL,4,Cwere not safe in court hearing
OL,6,FThe court heard how Mr Sawyer has been
OL,7,Fin social housing rent arrears, which
OL,8,Fthe defendant described as "quite a
OL,9,Flarge sum."
OL,11,F"The numbers simply do not add up for
OL,12,Fthe defendant in this case," concluded
OL,13,FMr Lewis.
OL,15,FHis defence is "a work of fiction, a
OL,16,Fsham, any word that fits," said Lewis,
OL,17,Fand the evidence shows Mr Sawyer's
OL,18,F"attempt to avoid the consequence of
OL,19,Fthis injunction".
OL,26,@pD@\OUqD@KO]sD@AOUtD@\O]wD@POUxD@ZO]zD@
